   "source": [
    "## 4. Normalization\n",
    "\n",
    "Before training the GCN, node features are standardized using only the training nodes.  \n",
    "This avoids data leakage, because the statistics used for normalization are computed exclusively from the training split and then applied to the whole graph.\n",
    "\n",
    "The graph is kept directed, preserving the original transaction direction provided by DGraphFin.  \n",
    "Finally, the complete PyTorch Geometric `Data` object is moved to the selected device, either GPU if available or CPU otherwise."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 210
    },
    "id": "v_A9gPhh3T-k",
    "outputId": "99cf19a9-1c6d-43c8-bcd5-d75c70f7952a"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Number of directed edges: 4,300,999\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Compute normalization statistics using training nodes only\n",
    "feature_mean = graph_data.x[graph_data.train_mask].mean(dim=0)\n",
    "feature_std = graph_data.x[graph_data.train_mask].std(dim=0).clamp(min=1e-8)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardize all node features using training statistics\n",
    "graph_data.x = (graph_data.x - feature_mean) / feature_std\n",
    "\n",
    "# Move the graph to the selected device\n",
    "graph_data = graph_data.to(device)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Number of directed edges: {graph_data.num_edges:,}\")"
   ]
  },
