   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "hQztH5oOLj9v"
   },
   "source": [
    "## 5. GCN Initialization and Class Weighting\n",
    "\n",
    "The GCN model is initialized using a compact set of hyperparameters.  \n",
    "The architecture outputs two classes, corresponding to legitimate and fraudulent nodes.\n",
    "\n",
    "Since the binary classification task is highly imbalanced, the training loss is weighted according to the class frequencies observed in the training split.  \n",
    "This gives a larger penalty to mistakes on the minority fraud class and helps the model avoid being biased toward the majority legitimate class."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
