    "id": "BoW2KPanLtPx"
   },
   "source": [
    "## 6. Target Fraud Node Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "Before applying the explainability methods, a target node must be selected.\n",
    "\n",
    "The objective is to explain a meaningful fraud prediction rather than an arbitrary node.  \n",
    "For this reason, the selection procedure first identifies the nodes whose true label is fraud and then gives priority to those that are also correctly predicted as fraud by the trained GCN.\n",
    "\n",
    "Among these candidates, the final target node is selected using a combined score based on:\n",
    "\n",
    "- the predicted fraud probability;\n",
    "- the local graph connectivity of the node.\n",
    "\n",
    "This makes the selected node suitable for explanation, because it is both confidently classified as fraud and embedded in a sufficiently informative graph neighborhood."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 426
    },
    "id": "-h-kJEhqM_hU",
    "outputId": "cc75983a-553d-4200-d725-0323d586d62f"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Selected target node: 624990\n",
      "In-degree: 67.0\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from torch_geometric.utils import degree\n",
    "\n",
    "# All fraud nodes\n",
    "fraud_nodes = (graph_data.y == 1).nonzero(as_tuple=True)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "in_deg = degree(graph_data.edge_index[1],num_nodes=graph_data.num_nodes)\n",
    "\n",
    "best_pos = torch.argmax(in_deg[fraud_nodes])\n",
    "node_idx = int(fraud_nodes[best_pos].item())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Selected target node:\", node_idx)\n",
    "print(\"In-degree:\", float(in_deg[node_idx].item()))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "X_TYYnqV8IVe"
   },
   "source": [
    "### 6.1 Local k-hop Subgraph Extraction\n",
    "\n",
    "Most node-level explainability methods operate on the local computation graph of the target node rather than on the full graph.\n",
    "\n",
    "For this reason, a `k`-hop subgraph is extracted around the selected fraud node.  \n",
    "The subgraph contains the nodes and directed edges that can contribute to the target prediction through message passing.\n",
    "\n",
    "A 3-hop neighborhood is used. This provides enough local context for the explainers while keeping the explanation problem computationally manageable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 426
    },
    "id": "YCorpHhfODji",
    "outputId": "1bbfe9e5-ac12-4aee-b657-d474f81c7014"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "k_hop = 3\n",
    "\n",
    "subset, sub_edge_index, mapping, edge_mask = k_hop_subgraph(\n",
    "    node_idx=node_idx,\n",
    "    num_hops = k_hop,\n",
    "    edge_index=graph_data.edge_index,\n",
    "    relabel_nodes=True,\n",
    "    num_nodes=graph_data.num_nodes,\n",
    "    flow=\"source_to_target\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "sub_x = graph_data.x[subset]\n",
    "\n",
    "target_sub_idx = int(mapping.item())\n",
    "target_node_id = int(subset[target_sub_idx].item())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute the degree of the target node inside the extracted subgraph\n",
    "sub_in_degree = degree(sub_edge_index[1], num_nodes=sub_x.size(0))\n",
    "\n",
    "sub_out_degree = degree(sub_edge_index[0], num_nodes=sub_x.size(0))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
