   ],
   "source": [
    "# Evaluate the trained model on the extracted local subgraph\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    out_sub = model(sub_x, sub_edge_index)\n",
    "    probs_sub = out_sub.exp()[target_sub_idx]\n",
    "    pred_sub = int(probs_sub.argmax().item())\n",
    "\n",
    "subgraph_summary = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"Property\": [\n",
    "            \"Number of hops\",\n",
    "            \"Subgraph nodes\",\n",
    "            \"Subgraph directed edges\",\n",
    "            \"Target local index\",\n",
    "            \"Target original node ID\",\n",
    "            \"Matches selected target node\",\n",
    "            \"Target local in-degree\",\n",
    "            \"Target local out-degree\",\n",
    "            \"True label\",\n",
    "            \"Predicted class\",\n",
    "            \"P(legitimate)\",\n",
    "            \"P(fraud)\",\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        \"Value\": [\n",
    "            k_hop,\n",
    "            int(sub_x.size(0)),\n",
    "            int(sub_edge_index.size(1)),\n",
    "            target_sub_idx,\n",
    "            target_node_id,\n",
    "            node_idx == target_node_id,\n",
    "            int(sub_in_degree[target_sub_idx].item()),\n",
    "            int(sub_out_degree[target_sub_idx].item()),\n",
    "            int(graph_data.y[target_node_id].item()),\n",
    "            pred_sub,\n",
    "            f\"{probs_sub[0].item():.4f}\",\n",
    "            f\"{probs_sub[1].item():.4f}\",\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "    }\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "display(subgraph_summary)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "iZ_AsWoM8bTA"
   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "The extracted 3-hop subgraph contains `89` nodes and `92` directed edges.  \n",
    "The selected target node is correctly mapped from the original graph to the local subgraph, with local index `23`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "kCmYEjAfOQf9"
   },
   "source": [
    "# 7. GNNExplainer\n",
    "\n",
    "The first explanation method applied to the selected fraud prediction is **GNNExplainer**.\n",
    "\n",
    "GNNExplainer learns a soft mask over the input graph in order to identify the components of the local computation graph that are most relevant for the model prediction.  \n",
    "In this implementation, the explanation is focused on **structural node importance** by using `node_mask_type=\"object\"`.\n",
    "\n",
    "This means that the explainer assigns an importance score to each node in the local subgraph, rather than explaining individual node features.  \n",
    "The edge mask is disabled in this experiment because edge-level gradients are not used in this GCN configuration.\n",
    "\n",
    "The resulting node mask will be used to identify which neighboring nodes contribute most to the fraud prediction of the target node.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 412
    },
    "id": "M5SHjWJ2OqLd",
    "outputId": "c39eaf16-dd73-4db6-e17d-b2d786e7a28d"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Explanation(node_mask=[89, 1], prediction=[89, 2], target=[89], index=[1], x=[89, 17], edge_index=[2, 92])\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from torch_geometric.explain import Explainer, GNNExplainer\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "\n",
    "gnn_explainer = Explainer(\n",
    "    model=model,\n",
    "    algorithm=GNNExplainer(epochs=100),\n",
    "    explanation_type=\"model\",\n",
    "    node_mask_type=\"object\",\n",
    "    edge_mask_type=None,\n",
    "    model_config={\n",
    "        \"mode\": \"multiclass_classification\",\n",
    "        \"task_level\": \"node\",\n",
    "        \"return_type\": \"log_probs\",\n",
    "    },\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "explanation_gnn = gnn_explainer(\n",
    "    sub_x,\n",
    "    sub_edge_index,\n",
    "    index=target_sub_idx,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "node_mask_gnn = explanation_gnn.node_mask.detach()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(explanation_gnn)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "_Jz6pP4m9fZD"
   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "GNNExplainer successfully produced an object-level node mask for the local 3-hop subgraph.\n",
    "\n",
    "The mask has shape `(89, 1)`, meaning that each node in the extracted subgraph receives one structural importance score.  \n",
    "The maximum importance value is approximately `0.7594`, while the mean importance is approximately `0.3740`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Most nodes receive a non-zero score, which suggests that the model prediction is influenced by a relatively broad portion of the local neighborhood.  \n",
    "The next step is to rank these nodes and inspect which ones are considered most relevant for the fraud prediction of the target node."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "P8lI1K3a9tR3"
   },
   "source": [
    "### 7.1 Derived Edge Importance Scores\n",
    "\n",
    "Since the GNNExplainer configuration used here focuses on object-level node importance, it does not directly produce an edge mask.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, for visualization purposes, an approximate edge importance score can be derived from the node importance scores.  \n",
    "For each directed edge, the score is computed as the average importance of its source and target nodes.\n",
    "\n",
    "These derived edge scores should not be interpreted as a true edge-level explanation learned by GNNExplainer.  \n",
    "They are only used to make the structural visualization more informative by highlighting connections between highly relevant nodes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 238
    },
    "id": "MzpDLR9cO5Mk",
    "outputId": "2bb90a36-0a07-42d8-a632-9ead2a69efb4"
