    "### 7.2 Top Important Nodes and Derived Edges\n",
    "\n",
    "The GNNExplainer node mask is used to rank the most important nodes in the local subgraph.\n",
    "\n",
    "The first table reports the top nodes according to their structural importance score.  \n",
    "For each node, both the local subgraph index and the original graph node ID are shown, together with the node label.\n",
    "\n",
    "The second table reports the top derived edge scores.  \n",
    "These edge scores are computed from the node importance values and are used only as a visualization aid, not as a direct edge-level explanation learned by GNNExplainer."
   ]
