   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "The highest-ranked nodes identified by GNNExplainer are not the target node itself, but neighboring nodes in its local computation graph.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is meaningful for a GCN-based prediction, because the representation of the target node is obtained by aggregating information from its neighbors.  \n",
    "Several of the most important nodes are labeled as legitimate or unknown, suggesting that the fraud prediction is not based only on the target node label, but also on the structural context around it.\n",
    "\n",
    "The derived edge ranking shows that all top edges point directly to the selected target node.  \n",
    "This is consistent with the local structure of the extracted subgraph, where the target node mainly receives incoming information from surrounding nodes.\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, the GNNExplainer result suggests that the fraud prediction is mostly influenced by a group of highly relevant incoming neighbors."
   ]
