   "source": [
    "# 9. Integrated Gradients\n",
    "\n",
    "Integrated Gradients requires a differentiable input with respect to which attribution scores can be computed.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here, edge-level importance is estimated by treating the edge weights of the local subgraph as differentiable inputs.  \n",
    "To avoid possible side effects from previous explainers, two clean GCN instances are created and initialized with the best trained checkpoint.\n",
    "\n",
    "A sanity check is then performed to verify that the reference GCN and the edge-weight compatible GCN produce identical predictions before Integrated Gradients is applied."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 129
    },
    "id": "All0IbvCEkeV",
    "outputId": "2a1fffdf-2bb3-4d9b-fbec-83ecc0612c18"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from torch_geometric.explain import Explainer, CaptumExplainer\n",
    "\n",
    "explainer_ig = Explainer(\n",
    "    model=model,\n",
    "    algorithm=CaptumExplainer(\"IntegratedGradients\"),\n",
    "    explanation_type=\"phenomenon\",\n",
    "    node_mask_type=\"attributes\",\n",
    "    edge_mask_type=None,\n",
    "    model_config=dict(\n",
    "        mode=\"multiclass_classification\",\n",
    "        task_level=\"node\",\n",
    "        return_type=\"log_probs\",\n",
    "    ),\n",
    ")\n",
    "target = torch.full((sub_x.size(0),), 1, dtype=torch.long, device=sub_x.device)\n",
    "\n",
    "explanation_ig = explainer_ig(\n",
    "    x=sub_x,\n",
    "    edge_index=sub_edge_index,\n",
    "    index=target_sub_idx,\n",
    "    target=target,  # fraud class per node\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
