   "source": [
    "\n",
    "The top-ranked Integrated Gradients edges all point directly to the selected target node.\n",
    "\n",
    "This confirms that the target prediction is strongly influenced by incoming structural information from neighboring nodes.  \n",
    "However, Integrated Gradients also provides additional information through the sign of the raw attribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "Some edges have a positive raw attribution, meaning that they increase the predicted fraud probability of the target node.  \n",
    "Other edges have a negative raw attribution, meaning that they push against the fraud prediction, even though they are still important in absolute terms.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
