    "The baseline fraud probability of the target node is `0.927401`. During optimization, the factual branch progressively preserves this prediction, reaching a final factual fraud probability close to the original value.  \n",
    "At the same time, the counterfactual branch reduces the fraud probability when the important nodes are removed, decreasing from approximately `0.7064` to `0.4575`.\n",
    "\n",
    "This behavior suggests that the learned node mask captures a set of structurally relevant nodes for the fraud prediction.  \n",
    "The final mask is normalized between `0` and `1`, with the target node forced to maximum relevance.\n",
    "\n",
    "The relatively high mask mean indicates that the explanation is not extremely sparse. Instead, the CausGNN-style objective identifies a broader group of influential nodes in the local subgraph."
   ]
