   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "The GraphEXT-style explainer successfully learned an edge-level structural mask for the selected target prediction.\n",
    "\n",
    "During optimization, the loss decreases progressively from `0.1976` to `0.0963`, while the predicted fraud probability increases from `0.8531` to `0.9448`.  \n",
    "This indicates that the learned edge mask is able to preserve, and even slightly strengthen, the fraud prediction of the target node.\n",
    "\n",
    "The mask mean also increases from approximately `0.4979` to `0.6255`, suggesting that the explainer keeps a moderately broad set of edges active rather than selecting only a very small subset.\n",
    "\n",
    "The final normalized edge mask has shape `(92,)`, assigning one importance score to each directed edge in the local subgraph.  \n",
    "The scores are normalized between `0` and `1`, with a final mean value of approximately `0.6381`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Almost all edges receive a non-zero score, with `91` non-zero importance edges out of `92`.  \n",
    "This suggests that the GraphEXT-style explanation is not extremely sparse, but it still provides a direct edge-level ranking that can be used to identify the most relevant structural connections supporting the fraud prediction."
   ]
  },
