   },
   "source": [
    "### 12.1 Top Important Edges\n",
    "\n",
    "The learned GraphEXT-style edge mask is used to rank the most important directed edges in the local subgraph.\n",
    "\n",
    "Each edge receives a normalized importance score between `0` and `1`.  \n",
    "The table reports the top-ranked edges, including both local subgraph indices and original DGraphFin node IDs.\n",
    "\n",
    "The column `Points to target node` is included to verify whether the most important edges directly connect to the selected fraud node."
   ]
