    "\n",
    "The highest-ranked edge has a normalized score of `1.0000` and directly connects node `1660417` to the selected target fraud node `624990`.  \n",
    "Most of the top-ranked edges also point directly to the target node, confirming that ORExplainer identifies incoming structural connections as highly relevant for preserving the fraud prediction.\n",
    "\n",
    "In particular, several important edges have the target node as destination, such as `2117851 → 624990`, `2088154 → 624990`, `1737014 → 624990`, `595614 → 624990`, `367206 → 624990`, and `1766657 → 624990`.\n",
    "\n",
    "At the same time, ORExplainer also assigns high scores to a few contextual edges that do not directly point to the target node, such as `1678337 → 1660417`, `3550474 → 2088154`, and `3543729 → 2088154`.  \n",
