  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "lw9X1MI8KJb1"
   },
   "source": [
    "### 14.1 GNNShap Explainer Initialization\n",
    "\n",
    "This cell initializes the GNNShap explainer using the trained GCN model.\n",
    "\n",
    "GNNShap requires a custom forward function that returns the class probabilities for a selected node.  \n",
    "Since the GCN model used in this notebook outputs log-probabilities, the forward function converts them back to probabilities using `.exp()`.\n",
    "\n",
    "The clean reference GCN is used to avoid side effects from previous explanation methods.  \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "3csBiMOPHYLQ"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def forward_no_edge_weight(model, node_features, edge_index, node_idx, edge_weight=None):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Forward function required by GNNShap.\"\"\"\n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        log_probs = model(node_features, edge_index)\n",
    "        probs = log_probs.exp()[node_idx, :]\n",
    "\n",
    "    return probs\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use the clean reference GCN\n",
    "model_gnnshap = model_reference.to(device)\n",
    "model_gnnshap.eval()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use the full DGraphFin graph, as in the reference implementation\n",
    "graph_data_gnnshap = graph_data.to(device)\n",
    "\n",
    "GNN_SHAP_HOPS = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "gshap = GNNShapExplainer(\n",
    "    model_gnnshap,\n",
    "    graph_data_gnnshap,\n",
    "    nhops=GNN_SHAP_HOPS,\n",
    "    verbose=0,\n",
    "    device=device,\n",
    "    forward_fn=forward_no_edge_weight,\n",
    "    progress_hide=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "gnnshap_init_summary = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"Property\": [\n",
    "            \"Explainer\",\n",
    "            \"Base model\",\n",
    "            \"Forward function\",\n",
    "            \"Number of hops\",\n",
    "            \"Device\",\n",
    "            \"Target original node ID\",\n",
    "            \"Target true label\",\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        \"Value\": [\n",
    "            \"GNNShapExplainer\",\n",
    "            \"Clean reference GCN\",\n",
    "            \"forward_no_edge_weight\",\n",
    "            GNN_SHAP_HOPS,\n",
    "            str(device),\n",
    "            target_node_id,\n",
    "            int(graph_data.y[target_node_id].item()),\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "    }\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "display(gnnshap_init_summary)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "vPMWjXywHp66"
   },
   "source": [
    "### 14.2 GNNShap Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "GNNShap is executed on the selected target fraud node.\n",
    "\n",
    "The method estimates Shapley-style contributions by sampling coalitions in the target node neighborhood.  \n",
    "The explanation is computed using the `SVXSampler` sampler and the `WLSSolver` solver, following the reference implementation.\n",
    "\n",
    "The number of samples controls the approximation quality.  \n",
    "A larger value gives more stable Shapley estimates but increases runtime."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "wdA7FI75GqCM"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "GNN_SHAP_NSAMPLES = 10000\n",
    "GNN_SHAP_BATCH_SIZE = 1024\n",
    "GNN_SHAP_SIZE_LIMIT = 3\n",
    "\n",
    "explanation_gshap = gshap.explain(\n",
    "    target_node_id,\n",
    "    nsamples=GNN_SHAP_NSAMPLES,\n",
    "    sampler_name=\"SVXSampler\",\n",
    "    batch_size=GNN_SHAP_BATCH_SIZE,\n",
    "    solver_name=\"WLSSolver\",\n",
    "    size_lim=GNN_SHAP_SIZE_LIMIT,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "gnnshap_result_summary = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"Property\": [\n",
    "            \"Explainer\",\n",
    "            \"Target original node ID\",\n",
    "            \"Number of samples\",\n",
    "            \"Sampler\",\n",
    "            \"Solver\",\n",
    "            \"Size limit\",\n",
    "            \"Returned object type\",\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        \"Value\": [\n",
    "            \"GNNShap\",\n",
    "            target_node_id,\n",
    "            GNN_SHAP_NSAMPLES,\n",
    "            \"SVXSampler\",\n",
    "            \"WLSSolver\",\n",
    "            GNN_SHAP_SIZE_LIMIT,\n",
    "            type(explanation_gshap).__name__,\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "    }\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "display(gnnshap_result_summary)"
   ]
  },
